  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I find wps pin on my galaxy S5 connected wifi?",
  "response": "To find the WPS PIN on your Galaxy S5 for a connected Wi-Fi network, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Settings**: Go to the home screen and tap on the \"Settings\" icon.\n\n2. **Wi-Fi Settings**: In the Settings menu, tap on \"Wi-Fi\".\n\n3. **Connected Network**: You should see the list of available Wi-Fi networks. Tap on the gear icon or settings icon next to the network you are currently connected to.\n\n4. **WPS PIN**: Look for an option labeled \"WPS push button\" or \"WPS PIN entry\". If your router supports WPS PIN entry, you might see a \"WPS PIN\" option. Tap on it, and your device will generate a unique 8-digit PIN.\n\n5. **Use the PIN**: You can then enter this PIN on your router's web interface to connect your device to the Wi-Fi network securely.\n\nPlease note that not all routers support WPS PIN entry, and some might only support WPS push button. If you don't see the WPS PIN option, you might need to use the WPS push button method or enter the Wi-Fi password manually.\n\nIf you're having trouble finding the WPS PIN or if it's not available, consider these alternatives:\n\n- **WPS Push Button**: If your router has a physical WPS button, you can press it and then, within two minutes, go to your Galaxy S5's Wi-Fi settings, tap on the connected network, and select \"WPS push button\" to connect.\n- **Manual Connection**: You can manually enter the Wi-Fi password found on your router or in your router's settings.\n\nIf you need further assistance, refer to your router's manual or contact your Internet Service Provider for support.",
